SIMPLE_SHELL(1)                  User Commands                 SIMPLE_SHELL(1)

NAME
       hsh - simple shell

SYNOPSIS
       hsh [command_file]

DESCRIPTION
       hsh is a simple UNIX command interpreter that reads commands from
       either standard input or from a file.

EXAMPLES
       Interactive mode:
              $ ./hsh
              ($) /bin/ls
              ($) exit
              $

       Non-interactive mode:
              $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

AUTHORS
       See AUTHORS file.

